  <h5> The Burning Fire </h5>
     <h2> <id="blurb"> The American Criminal Justice System "is designed to deliver justice for all.  This means protecting the innocent, convicting criminals, and providing a fair justice process to help keep order across the country.” The criminal justice system is on fire, and it is a roaring dumpster fire of injustice is the one firing it. However, not all Americans are affected equally by its fire. Rather, the marginalized and politically disenfranchised, particularly communities of color, bear the brunt of this injustice. The cops, who are meant to keep us secure, are targeting, threatening, and oppresing countless POC  all over America. Countless people are racially profiled by this systematic system, which often times result in ones innocence revoked by the  police’s use of deadly force. The burning criminal justice system has promised to deliver "justice for all"  to the innocnet but  the criminals, the police get a free pass with murder and the innocent are left failed yet again
</h2>
